========== 02/26/18 ==========
==============================

I) === Summary: ===
	A) Added Push Notification Plugin to WordPress
	B) Started Setup Push Notification plugin for Android
	C) Started setup Push Notifications within Android
	D) Created Firebase project for push notifications
	E) Set official colors

II) === Takeaways: ===
	- WordPress Plugin send a message to firebase which sends the message to all phones who registered using the app id (com.transyrambler.rambler) and their instance id
	- DeviceRegistrationFirebase.java = registration
		- Not working properly
	- MessageHandlerFirebase.java = handle messages
		- Not work properly
	- The firebase is set up with my personal email since it wouldn't let me make an account with my transy email
	- The test notification I sent apparently went to two devices, so it looks like registration is working (both the emulator and my phone)
	- Not seeing the log statements in Logcat though...
		- therefore don't know if the MessageHandling is working
	- Changing the app ID might have messed things up
		- most of the app is in `java > com > brendansapps.rambler` -just the MessageHandler is in `java > com > transyrambler.rambler`

III) === Resources: ===
	- https://delitestudio.com/wordpress/push-notifications-for-wordpress/configuring-android-push-notifications/
	- https://firebase.google.com/docs/cloud-messaging/android/start/
	- https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nwUVq2UPQM8

III) === Log: ===

A) Added Push Notification Plugin to WordPress
	- Getting to the WordPress Dashboard for the staging site
		1) Log into GoDaddy
		2) My Products
		3) Managed WordPress -> Manage All
		4) www.transyrambler.com -> staging -> Manage
		5) Staging WP Admin
	- Added plugin
		1) Plugins -> Add New
		2) Search "Push Notifications"
		3) Install Now "Push Notifications for WordPress (Lite)" by Delite Studio S.r.l.

B) Setup Android Push Notifications from WordPress plugin
	- Get to staging site WordPress Dashboard
	- Push Notifications -> Settings -> Android
	- Check box "send push notifications to Android devices"
	- Set Server Key (see part C)


C) Setting up Push Notifications within Android
	- https://delitestudio.com/wordpress/push-notifications-for-wordpress/configuring-android-push-notifications/
	- https://firebase.google.com/docs/cloud-messaging/android/start/
	- https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nwUVq2UPQM8
	1) Create a Firebase project online (see part D)
	2) Set Application ID
		- build.gradle
		- com.transyrambler.rambler
	3) Add Firebase to the App
		- tools -> Firebase
		- connect to existing -> Transylvania Rambler
			- Because I already did section D
	4) Add FCM to the app
		- automatically added two dependencies to the files
	5) Handle InstanceID Registration
		- Right Click on (app>java>com.brendansapp.rambler)-> New -> Java Class
		- DeviceRegistrationFirebase
		- extends FirebaseInstanceIdService
		- override onTokenRefresh()
			- Gets the token but does not yet registered it with the server
	6) Handle Messages
		- Right Click on (app>java>com.brendansapp.rambler)-> New -> Service
		- MessageHandlerFirebase\
		- extends FirebaseMessagingService
		- override onMessageReceived
			- check from, data, and notification fields

D) Created Firebase project online for push notifications
	- used brenthompson2@gmail.com
	- "Transylvania Rambler"

E) Set Official Colors
    <color name="colorPrimary">#9D2336</color>
